Client should be able to withstand memory attacks as well as not leak any secrets.

Also it should wipe memory upon plugging in a device or w.e. (anti-forensics).

CFG file brute force attacks should be mitigated by using a wipe logic that clears sensitive data after a certain number of failed attempts.

Auto wipe memory after a certain period of inactivity.

If usb device is unplugged = wipe memory?

CFG file only decrypted on demand and immedietly encrypted again

Messages should be encrypted with the following schema:

KEY = SEED + RANDOM_START_INDEX + MESSAGE_INDEX (user A has even indexes, and user B has odd indexes)